WEBVTT

00:01.502 --> 00:03.435
[dog barking in distance]

00:03.570 --> 00:05.703
Adult mark:<i> Our family didn't</i>
<i>like to talk about the past.</i>

00:05.740 --> 00:06.838
Pop?

00:06.874 --> 00:08.674
Uh, when did your father die?

00:08.676 --> 00:11.510
Uh, 1896.

00:11.512 --> 00:13.812
He drowned when I was two.

00:13.814 --> 00:15.647
He was a whaler.

00:15.649 --> 00:17.816
The whale won.

00:17.885 --> 00:19.385
Adult mark:<i> Mostly because</i>
<i> there wasn't much</i>

00:19.520 --> 00:20.652
<i> Good to talk about.</i>

00:20.721 --> 00:21.920
And his father?

00:21.922 --> 00:23.688
Drowned.

00:23.758 --> 00:24.856
And his?

00:24.892 --> 00:26.325
Lost at sea.

00:26.460 --> 00:27.726
Why?

00:27.728 --> 00:29.928
It's homework.
We have to do a family tree.

00:29.930 --> 00:32.931
Good god, what would you
want to do a family tree for?

00:33.000 --> 00:35.133
You spend all that time
and money trying to find out

00:35.169 --> 00:37.169
Where you came from,
and then you spend twice as much

00:37.304 --> 00:38.637
Trying to cover it
all back up again!

00:38.772 --> 00:40.405
Adult mark:<i> The only time</i>
<i> my parents looked back</i>

00:40.441 --> 00:41.740
<i> Was to toss some salt</i>
<i> over their shoulder.</i>

00:41.875 --> 00:43.108
Oh, mom?

00:43.110 --> 00:46.612
When did your mother die?

00:46.614 --> 00:49.147
It's not nice to
talk about the dead.

00:49.183 --> 00:50.983
I'm going to bed.

00:51.118 --> 00:52.684
What?

00:52.820 --> 00:53.885
Pop: Sorry, son.

00:53.954 --> 00:56.221
Our family tree
is more like a shrub.

00:56.257 --> 00:58.757
An over-watered one at that.
[phone rings]

00:58.759 --> 01:01.493
Mike sr: Good god, who's calling
the house at this hour?

01:01.562 --> 01:04.163
Pop: See, the critches were
fishermen from liverpool.

01:04.298 --> 01:07.332
Now, my brother moses,
he didn't drown!

01:07.368 --> 01:09.134
He died of tb.

01:09.136 --> 01:10.635
Pop: Put that in there.
Mark: Yeah.

01:10.704 --> 01:11.837
Pop: That's important.

01:11.972 --> 01:14.039
What's that again?

01:14.041 --> 01:15.240
Brendan...?

01:15.242 --> 01:16.841
Oh?

01:16.877 --> 01:18.544
Adult mark:<i> Uncle brendan</i>
<i> was a travelling salesman.</i>

01:18.679 --> 01:20.011
<i> He was always in trouble.</i>

01:20.013 --> 01:21.380
What's he done now?

01:21.515 --> 01:23.515
It's not the police, is it?

01:23.650 --> 01:26.385
Oh, it's probably somebody
looking for money.

01:26.387 --> 01:28.953
Adult mark:<i> But he</i> was
<i> still pop's favourite.</i>

01:29.089 --> 01:30.322
Just say he isn't here.

01:30.324 --> 01:31.356
He isn't here!

01:31.492 --> 01:33.659
Ah, look,
I haven't seen brendan in...

01:33.794 --> 01:35.761
Let me have that again?

01:35.763 --> 01:38.397
[indecipherable voice on phone]

01:38.532 --> 01:40.932
Oh, uh...

01:41.001 --> 01:43.268
Okay, well,
thanks for letting us know.

01:43.337 --> 01:45.537
Goodbye.

01:45.672 --> 01:46.939
Well, what is it?

01:46.941 --> 01:49.607
What's the trouble
the boy's got into now?

01:52.880 --> 01:54.146
He's dead.

01:54.148 --> 01:56.348
♪

01:56.483 --> 01:57.816
Wha...?

01:57.951 --> 02:01.019
♪

02:01.021 --> 02:03.421
Adult mark:<i> My family tree</i>
<i> was losing leaves</i>

02:03.423 --> 02:06.024
<i> Like it was the windiest</i>
<i> day in autumn.</i>

02:06.026 --> 02:09.494
♪

02:09.497 --> 02:13.298
♪

02:13.367 --> 02:16.768
♪

02:16.904 --> 02:19.271
Adult mark:<i> The critch family</i>
<i> plot was close to bursting,</i>

02:19.340 --> 02:21.706
<i> But there was just enough</i>
<i> room for uncle brendan</i>

02:21.708 --> 02:24.176
<i> To slip in like the missing</i>
<i> piece of a puzzle.</i>

02:24.178 --> 02:27.145
Mary: Mike... Shouldn't
somebody say something?

02:36.723 --> 02:39.391
Uncle brendan...

02:39.460 --> 02:42.327
Uncle brendan was, um...

02:45.633 --> 02:48.400
He was...

02:48.469 --> 02:51.403
♪

02:51.538 --> 02:52.604
Adult mark:<i> Try as I might,</i>

02:52.739 --> 02:54.406
<i> I just couldn't</i>
<i> make the tears come.</i>

02:54.408 --> 02:57.876
<i>And try as he might, my brother</i>
<i> just couldn't stop them.</i>

02:58.011 --> 02:59.745
♪

02:59.880 --> 03:02.314
Come on.

03:02.316 --> 03:04.249
I just spoke to bucky.

03:04.251 --> 03:07.685
He tells me that
the grave is packed tight.

03:07.721 --> 03:09.955
The only way we're gonna
get poor brendan in there

03:10.024 --> 03:11.957
Is if we stick him in sideways.

03:12.026 --> 03:13.091
Good god!

03:13.160 --> 03:15.026
Shh, keep it down!

03:15.095 --> 03:18.496
Geez.

03:18.498 --> 03:22.100
I always thought that I'd be
in there alongside your mother.

03:22.169 --> 03:24.302
What about me?

03:24.438 --> 03:26.638
This is not about you.

03:26.773 --> 03:28.840
This is about me!

03:28.876 --> 03:32.244
[crying in background]

03:35.382 --> 03:37.515
You go ahead, dad.
I'll make sure it's done.

03:37.585 --> 03:38.884
You sure?

03:38.886 --> 03:41.053
Yeah.

03:41.055 --> 03:43.788
Alright, everyone.
Nothing to see here.

03:43.790 --> 03:46.958
Got some tiny sandwiches
up at the house.

03:46.961 --> 03:48.660
Alice: Come on, girl.

03:48.662 --> 03:51.863
We checks in on our crowd
before we goes.

03:54.034 --> 03:57.869
♪

03:57.871 --> 04:00.138
Bucky: Well, mike, b'y.

04:00.273 --> 04:03.475
Hard losing a brother, eh?

04:03.544 --> 04:06.878
You must be torn apart.

04:06.947 --> 04:08.613
Hm.

04:08.616 --> 04:11.616
♪

04:11.652 --> 04:14.886
Adult mark:<i> A cemetery trip</i>
<i>was a family archivist's dream.</i>

04:14.888 --> 04:18.056
<i> I couldn't see the forest</i>
<i> for the family trees.</i>

04:18.058 --> 04:19.891
Mark: Uh, mom?

04:20.027 --> 04:21.226
Mary: Yes, my love?

04:21.361 --> 04:23.961
Where's my grandmother?
Her name's not on here.

04:24.098 --> 04:26.030
Why would her name be there?
She's not--

04:26.032 --> 04:28.966
Say a prayer, alice.
You'll be in there soon enough.

04:29.003 --> 04:30.502
[sobbing]

04:30.504 --> 04:32.370
They just never
added her name is all.

04:32.439 --> 04:33.905
She was a very...

04:33.974 --> 04:36.140
Private person.

04:36.176 --> 04:38.944
Now, give it up being morbid.
You're on me last nerve.

04:38.946 --> 04:42.314
Alice, we're gone.

04:42.316 --> 04:44.249
Fine, stay and water
the flowers.

04:44.384 --> 04:45.917
Adult mark:<i> Like bucky</i>
<i> the gravedigger,</i>

04:45.986 --> 04:48.152
<i> The more I dug,</i>
<i> the more I uncovered.</i>

04:50.157 --> 04:53.391
Oh, now, look who's
decided to show up.

04:53.460 --> 04:54.926
Fashionably late!

04:54.928 --> 04:56.328
I was burying my brother!

04:56.463 --> 04:57.929
Sideways!

04:57.931 --> 05:00.198
Next to my mother, whose
coffin has held up pretty well,

05:00.200 --> 05:01.232
By the way!

05:01.302 --> 05:03.134
Boo-hoo-hoo, ya big poodle.

05:03.203 --> 05:06.071
You couldn't even let your
brother have his special day!

05:06.140 --> 05:09.107
Do you know what it was like
for me to have to see all that?

05:09.176 --> 05:11.910
No, because I was here
entertaining our company!

05:12.045 --> 05:15.947
I don't mean to interrupt,
but, uh, mr. Critch...

05:16.016 --> 05:18.750
Mike is the only son
you have left.

05:18.786 --> 05:21.419
It's too late
to change the past,

05:21.555 --> 05:24.022
But it isn't too late
to adjust the future.

05:24.157 --> 05:25.623
Ooh, jam-jams!

05:25.659 --> 05:28.894
Don't mind if I do!

05:28.896 --> 05:30.428
Yummy, yummy.

05:30.564 --> 05:33.031
Okay.

05:33.166 --> 05:36.835
Was I really a bad father?

05:36.837 --> 05:38.837
Oh, no, dad.
Brendan loved you.

05:38.906 --> 05:40.505
No, I don't mean to him.

05:40.574 --> 05:43.308
I mean to you.

05:43.443 --> 05:46.578
Oh.
Well, uh...

05:46.713 --> 05:47.913
You did your best, dad.

05:48.048 --> 05:50.315
No, no.

05:50.317 --> 05:52.718
No, I didn't.

05:52.853 --> 05:56.120
It's too late for me
and brendan and me now, but...

05:56.156 --> 05:59.658
It's not too late for you and I.

05:59.793 --> 06:01.626
Come on.

06:01.662 --> 06:03.061
Mark: Mom?
Mary: What, honey?

06:03.196 --> 06:04.396
What did my grandmother
die from?

06:04.531 --> 06:05.564
Jesus murphy!

06:05.566 --> 06:07.932
Have we not had
enough death for one day?

06:07.934 --> 06:09.367
Go make yourself useful!

06:09.370 --> 06:11.402
Pass out those wieners!

06:11.438 --> 06:13.538
Adult mark:<i> It was unlike</i>
<i> my mother not to gossip</i>

06:13.540 --> 06:14.472
<i> About someone.</i>

06:14.541 --> 06:15.674
<i> Something was up.</i>

06:15.809 --> 06:16.908
Mark: Vienna sausage?

06:17.043 --> 06:18.676
Ooh, viennese!

06:18.712 --> 06:20.678
We don't get these
in the rectory.

06:20.714 --> 06:22.948
Mark: Father, I'm researching
my family tree

06:22.950 --> 06:24.682
And I'm missing some leaves.

06:24.718 --> 06:26.685
Does the church
have births, deaths?

06:26.820 --> 06:28.019
That kind of thing?

06:28.154 --> 06:29.855
Well, all that information
is kind of private.

06:29.857 --> 06:34.426
It's not really for kids.

06:34.428 --> 06:36.361
Well, I...

06:36.496 --> 06:38.029
I guess I could supervise?

06:38.065 --> 06:39.965
Yeah.

06:40.100 --> 06:41.999
There's plenty more
where that came from.

06:42.035 --> 06:43.568
[thud]

06:43.637 --> 06:45.503
Pop: Use the bloody mitt!

06:45.572 --> 06:47.906
Adult mark:<i> Pop was determined</i>
<i> to make up for lost time,</i>

06:47.908 --> 06:49.107
<i> And with dad,</i>

06:49.242 --> 06:51.910
<i> That meant starting over</i>
<i> at the beginning.</i>

06:51.979 --> 06:55.313
Pop: You sure you don't
want to take your jacket off?

06:55.382 --> 06:57.715
Nice and easy!

06:57.751 --> 06:58.783
Oh!

06:58.819 --> 07:00.418
Pop: Augh.
Jesus.

07:00.421 --> 07:02.988
Come on, this is wasted time!

07:03.123 --> 07:05.623
Adult mark:<i> Dislike father,</i>
<i> dislike son.</i>

07:08.929 --> 07:11.529
[school bell rings]

07:15.869 --> 07:19.670
♪

07:19.706 --> 07:22.007
Adult mark:<i> Even jesus had</i>
<i> a more detailed family tree</i>

07:22.142 --> 07:25.009
<i> Than I did!</i>

07:25.045 --> 07:28.213
♪

07:28.282 --> 07:29.814
♪

07:29.883 --> 07:31.749
Whoa!
Nice tree.

07:31.819 --> 07:33.351
Very full.

07:33.387 --> 07:34.986
Photo albums,
arrest records.

07:34.988 --> 07:36.121
It was easy.

07:36.256 --> 07:38.223
How's yours?

07:38.225 --> 07:39.757
I'm just having a little trouble

07:39.793 --> 07:41.493
Finding out where
my grandmother is.

07:41.628 --> 07:43.161
I don't really know
my nan either.

07:43.296 --> 07:44.663
Yeah, dad cashed
her pension cheques

07:44.798 --> 07:45.163
Yeah, dad cashed
her pension cheques

07:45.899 --> 07:46.430
So she's super pissed.

07:46.467 --> 07:50.067
Shut up, nimrod!

07:50.103 --> 07:51.336
Maybe we could help.

07:51.405 --> 07:53.271
That'd be great!

07:53.307 --> 07:54.706
I have a lead.

07:54.775 --> 07:57.642
We will leave
no tombstone unturned.

07:57.644 --> 07:59.377
♪

07:59.413 --> 08:02.246
Radio:<i> At coles funeral home,</i>
<i> we want to help you to...</i>

08:02.282 --> 08:05.650
Who should
we leave the oven to?

08:05.686 --> 08:07.051
What?

08:07.087 --> 08:08.987
The oven.
Who should get it?

08:08.989 --> 08:10.655
Why are you writing a will?

08:10.657 --> 08:12.990
The only one that gets
any of our stuff when we dies

08:13.026 --> 08:14.725
Is the bank.

08:14.761 --> 08:17.395
Why don't you just tell the boy
where his grandmother is?

08:17.464 --> 08:19.865
No need to go
stirring all that up.

08:20.000 --> 08:21.533
Let dead dogs lie.

08:21.535 --> 08:22.667
[front door opens]

08:22.802 --> 08:23.869
You can't change the past.

08:24.004 --> 08:26.404
[front door closes]

08:26.473 --> 08:30.008
We are gonna do something
we should have done years ago.

08:30.143 --> 08:34.546
I'm gonna teach you how to fish.

08:34.548 --> 08:36.214
[sighs]
pop: Come on.

08:36.349 --> 08:38.883
You'll love it.

08:38.886 --> 08:41.619
Mary: Sorry.

08:41.621 --> 08:44.889
[dog barking and bird calling
in distance]

08:44.958 --> 08:48.492
[music playing on radio]

08:48.529 --> 08:52.163
<i> ♪</i> in every life
we have some trouble. ♪

08:52.165 --> 08:54.766
♪ but if you worry
you makes it double. ♪

08:54.835 --> 08:58.169
♪ don't worry!

08:58.171 --> 09:01.038
♪ be happy!

09:01.074 --> 09:02.307
Jesus, mike.

09:02.309 --> 09:03.341
Don't worry!

09:03.377 --> 09:06.778
Be happy!

09:06.847 --> 09:10.348
<i> ♪ don't worry...</i>

09:10.417 --> 09:14.052
<i> ♪ be happy...</i>

09:14.187 --> 09:15.920
<i> ♪ don't worry, be happy.</i>

09:15.989 --> 09:17.255
<i> ♪ woo...</i>

09:17.390 --> 09:18.456
[door opens]

09:18.592 --> 09:21.559
Frig, mike.
What's wrong?

09:21.595 --> 09:25.263
I miss uncle brendan.

09:25.332 --> 09:28.399
You know, he just got me,
and now he's just gone,

09:28.435 --> 09:30.435
And it's not fair.

09:30.437 --> 09:32.003
It never is.

09:32.005 --> 09:34.339
Brendan was good for a laugh.

09:34.408 --> 09:36.207
He wouldn't want to
see you like this.

09:36.209 --> 09:37.409
Oh...

09:37.544 --> 09:39.543
Geez, yeah,
he'd be pretty embarrassed, huh?

09:39.580 --> 09:43.682
No, b'y.

09:43.817 --> 09:46.618
I never seen anyone take
to this place as quick as you.

09:46.620 --> 09:49.154
Brendan would be proud
to be your uncle.

09:49.289 --> 09:52.156
I know I would be.

09:55.161 --> 09:56.828
Look, I got ya something
I been meaning to give ya.

09:56.897 --> 09:59.030
Oh, yeah?
What is it?

09:59.099 --> 10:00.365
Dick: Not much time
left in this song.

10:00.367 --> 10:02.667
Hang on.

10:06.773 --> 10:07.905
Mike jr: No way!

10:07.975 --> 10:10.908
You earned it.

10:10.978 --> 10:16.648
Well, come on!
Try it on!

10:16.717 --> 10:20.852
<i> ♪ don't worry...</i>

10:20.921 --> 10:22.654
Oh!

10:22.723 --> 10:26.625
Thanks... Uncle dick.

10:26.760 --> 10:27.859
Oh...

10:27.928 --> 10:30.495
Jesus.

10:30.564 --> 10:32.897
[both sobbing]

10:32.933 --> 10:35.400
[church bell tolls]

10:35.469 --> 10:38.202
♪

10:38.271 --> 10:39.804
Adult mark:<i> Even priests</i>
<i> can be tempted.</i>

10:39.939 --> 10:41.539
Hey, you kids gotta hurry up.

10:41.675 --> 10:46.811
If brother angel comes back,
he'll crucify me.

10:46.813 --> 10:48.146
I can't find her anywhere!

10:48.148 --> 10:49.414
She's a ghost.

10:49.416 --> 10:50.615
Ritche: That's the point.

10:50.750 --> 10:51.850
She's dead.

10:51.985 --> 10:54.886
Do you mind?
She's still my grandmother.

10:54.955 --> 10:58.490
She has to be in here somewhere.
We found her birth certificate.

10:58.625 --> 11:01.292
What's this all about, anyway?

11:01.361 --> 11:04.295
My mom says
her mom's buried in our plot,

11:04.297 --> 11:05.630
But I can't find her...

11:05.632 --> 11:07.298
There or anywhere.

11:07.300 --> 11:09.601
Well, there's
an explanation for everything.

11:09.603 --> 11:12.670
Like turning water into wine?

11:12.706 --> 11:15.239
Well, there might be more
info in the parish sectretum,

11:15.275 --> 11:17.909
But that's off-limits.

11:17.978 --> 11:19.911
Please, father?
Just this once?

11:19.913 --> 11:21.346
I'm sorry, buddy.

11:21.481 --> 11:23.448
I wish I could help, but even
I don't know what's in there.

11:23.583 --> 11:25.649
Found it!

11:25.686 --> 11:26.651
Holy crap!

11:26.720 --> 11:27.719
Oh, no.

11:27.854 --> 11:28.919
Uh...

11:28.955 --> 11:30.188
Okay, give that to me.

11:30.190 --> 11:31.790
Fox: No.
Father garcia: I... Give it.

11:31.925 --> 11:34.125
Fox: Why would I--
father garcia: Give it to me.

11:34.260 --> 11:35.459
What's it say?

11:35.495 --> 11:38.063
Nothing, it's stupid.

11:38.198 --> 11:39.631
Your nan was divorced!

11:39.766 --> 11:41.132
Adult mark:<i> Divorce!</i>

11:41.134 --> 11:43.735
<i> The only catholic</i>
<i> "d" word worse than death!</i>

11:43.737 --> 11:45.603
And she re-married!

11:45.672 --> 11:47.806
But catholics can't remarry.

11:47.808 --> 11:49.741
She changed religions?

11:49.743 --> 11:52.744
So we just have to check the
protestant cemetery now, right?

11:52.746 --> 11:54.145
No.

11:54.147 --> 11:55.480
She won't be there.

11:55.549 --> 11:58.549
Why not?

11:58.585 --> 11:59.684
Because she's not dead!

11:59.819 --> 12:02.420
[coughs]
jesus christ!

12:06.126 --> 12:08.392
...Be with you.

12:11.732 --> 12:14.165
♪

12:14.167 --> 12:16.901
♪

12:17.036 --> 12:20.171
Pop: I should have taught you
how to fish years ago!

12:20.173 --> 12:21.372
Mike sr: What?

12:21.441 --> 12:23.908
I can't hear anything
over that bloody engine.

12:23.944 --> 12:25.976
Make and break!

12:26.012 --> 12:28.847
Old and reliable, just like me.

12:28.982 --> 12:31.115
♪

12:31.184 --> 12:32.117
Fisherman: Waddaya at?

12:32.252 --> 12:34.786
Asshole.

12:34.921 --> 12:36.253
I wish we were on that one!

12:36.289 --> 12:37.989
What?

12:38.124 --> 12:40.391
Forget it,
ya deaf old coot!

12:40.460 --> 12:41.626
[laughs]
exactly!

12:41.761 --> 12:43.961
Alright, sit down, lad.

12:44.030 --> 12:46.931
Pop: Okay, here we go.

12:46.933 --> 12:50.468
♪

12:50.537 --> 12:53.938
♪

12:53.974 --> 12:54.939
Mark: Mom?

12:54.975 --> 12:56.207
Christ on a cracker!

12:56.276 --> 12:57.342
You scared
the bejesus out of me!

12:57.477 --> 12:58.409
I have a question.

12:58.478 --> 13:00.478
I don't want to hear it.

13:00.613 --> 13:02.346
You come from
a long line of dead people.

13:02.415 --> 13:03.982
That's all you need to know.

13:03.984 --> 13:06.317
I promise I won't ask where
my grandmother is buried again.

13:06.452 --> 13:09.420
[exhales]
thank god for that.

13:09.422 --> 13:12.123
So, where does she live?

13:14.027 --> 13:15.493
Enough!

13:15.628 --> 13:17.795
I got that much to do today, I--

13:17.831 --> 13:19.897
Stop lying!

13:19.933 --> 13:22.567
She isn't dead!
She isn't even catholic!

13:22.702 --> 13:26.370
What kind of mother lies about
a kid's grandmother being dead?

13:26.406 --> 13:29.574
Well, she's dead to me.

13:29.576 --> 13:33.444
"what kind of mother?"
wow!

13:33.513 --> 13:35.579
The kind of mother
who didn't have one, I guess.

13:35.615 --> 13:37.114
Mom, please.
Please...

13:37.150 --> 13:40.784
Mary: Oh...

13:40.821 --> 13:44.922
The only thing I ever wanted
to keep from you was pain.

13:44.991 --> 13:48.259
My parents got divorced
when I was seven years old.

13:48.261 --> 13:52.730
The nuns looked at me like
I was the devil's own, which...

13:52.799 --> 13:54.532
I s'pose I was.

13:54.667 --> 13:56.334
Mom, I'm sorry, I won't...

13:56.469 --> 13:59.838
Oh, duckie, I don't want to be
the kind of mother who lies.

13:59.973 --> 14:02.573
I had enough of that myself.

14:02.609 --> 14:04.409
♪

14:04.544 --> 14:06.010
Mary: So...

14:06.145 --> 14:06.411
Mary: So...

14:07.581 --> 14:10.281
One day my mother
just packed a bag and left,

14:10.317 --> 14:13.685
Like she was going to the store.

14:13.820 --> 14:15.286
I begged her to
take me with her,

14:15.421 --> 14:17.621
But she just pushed me down

14:17.657 --> 14:20.024
And told me to stay where I was.

14:20.026 --> 14:21.292
And told me to stay where I was.

14:21.328 --> 14:25.129
And being a good girl,
I listened to her.

14:25.131 --> 14:28.499
I never saw hide nor hair
of my mother again.

14:28.568 --> 14:30.702
Adult mark:<i> Looking at</i>
<i>the hurt in my mother's eyes,</i>

14:30.837 --> 14:35.673
<i> I realized that some things</i>
<i> stay buried for a reason.</i>

14:35.675 --> 14:38.576
You want to know
where she is?

14:38.645 --> 14:42.914
She married a clark
and she lives on forest road.

14:43.049 --> 14:45.449
But... You said
never to go there.

14:45.485 --> 14:47.185
"nothing but skeets
and hussies."

14:47.187 --> 14:50.120
I didn't lie to you about that.

14:50.156 --> 14:52.990
♪

14:53.026 --> 14:54.792
You knew where she was
all this time

14:54.861 --> 14:56.660
And you never even called her?

14:56.696 --> 14:59.664
She's your mother!

14:59.666 --> 15:02.800
I know when I'm not wanted.

15:04.771 --> 15:06.804
Adult mark:<i> If there was</i>
<i> one thing I was good at,</i>

15:06.873 --> 15:09.107
<i> It was making things worse.</i>

15:09.242 --> 15:10.942
Pop: Alright,
let it hit the bottom,

15:11.011 --> 15:13.778
Bring it up a couple of feet,
and then start jigging.

15:13.780 --> 15:14.912
That's what I'm doing!

15:14.914 --> 15:16.213
Jerk it!

15:16.249 --> 15:17.849
Ya jerk,
don't you know anything?

15:17.984 --> 15:21.018
I s'pose if brendan was here now
he'd just walk out on the water

15:21.087 --> 15:23.021
And the fish would just
start jumpin' in the boat?

15:23.156 --> 15:25.089
Pop: Alright!
Oh...

15:25.224 --> 15:28.893
Oh, you've got it caught on
the bottom, you bloody jinker!

15:28.895 --> 15:30.361
You're the one
with the jigger!

15:30.430 --> 15:31.963
You know,
this was a mistake.

15:31.965 --> 15:33.131
Here...

15:33.266 --> 15:34.898
We can finally agree
on something for once.

15:34.935 --> 15:38.636
[engine sputters]

15:38.705 --> 15:41.705
Pop: Oh, jesus, now...

15:41.741 --> 15:43.775
It's completely seized.

15:43.910 --> 15:45.743
Ah, I can't move that.

15:45.745 --> 15:46.744
Can't you fix it?

15:46.780 --> 15:48.078
Fix it?

15:48.114 --> 15:50.447
I don't know anything
about boats!

15:50.483 --> 15:52.116
Mike sr: Well, what
are we gonna do now?

15:52.118 --> 15:53.985
We're drifting out to sea!

15:53.987 --> 15:57.121
I suppose it's the critch curse,
finally caught up with us.

15:57.157 --> 15:58.389
Well, it figures.

15:58.524 --> 16:00.324
And the plot's full.

16:07.033 --> 16:09.567
Fox: That must be her.

16:09.636 --> 16:11.402
Adult mark:<i> I was laying eyes</i>
<i> on my grandmother</i>

16:11.471 --> 16:13.204
<i> For the first time...</i>

16:13.206 --> 16:14.939
<i> In a stakeout!</i>

16:15.074 --> 16:17.742
Ritche: I bet those bags
are full of grandma stuff.

16:17.811 --> 16:20.011
Like cookies and hard candy!

16:20.146 --> 16:21.946
What are you gonna do?

16:22.081 --> 16:23.081
I'm going in.

16:23.216 --> 16:24.215
Fox: Wait.

16:24.350 --> 16:25.483
This doesn't feel right.

16:25.552 --> 16:27.084
Ritche: What, are you crazy?

16:27.153 --> 16:28.920
She's his grandma!

16:29.055 --> 16:31.756
She's gonna hug him
and feed him and kiss him.

16:31.891 --> 16:33.157
Trust me.

16:33.226 --> 16:36.394
Not all families are like
the ones you see on tv.

16:36.529 --> 16:38.562
I'm not doing this for me.

16:38.631 --> 16:40.964
I'm doing it for mom.

16:46.473 --> 16:49.840
[emotional music]

16:49.876 --> 16:52.243
Mark sr.: When's
brendan's birthday?

16:52.312 --> 16:54.312
You don't know when your
own brother's birthday is?

16:54.447 --> 16:57.248
October 2nd.

16:57.250 --> 17:00.451
And when's mine?

17:00.586 --> 17:02.219
What?

17:02.255 --> 17:03.754
Oh...

17:03.757 --> 17:07.658
In the summer.

17:07.660 --> 17:08.525
What?

17:12.232 --> 17:16.133
Look, I was easier on brendan

17:16.269 --> 17:18.735
Because he needed me more.

17:18.772 --> 17:20.338
You were...

17:20.340 --> 17:23.841
You were more self-sufficient
and you didn't need me.

17:23.877 --> 17:27.945
And now, I mean, do you know
how hard it is for a father

17:28.014 --> 17:29.881
To be dependent on his son?

17:29.883 --> 17:31.015
Dad, it's not like that.

17:31.150 --> 17:33.050
I never had a father.

17:33.119 --> 17:36.653
I didn't know what
it was to be one.

17:36.689 --> 17:40.024
But seeing you with your boys...

17:40.159 --> 17:41.759
Now I know.

17:41.894 --> 17:44.028
You are a great grandfather.

17:44.163 --> 17:46.364
Ah, well...

17:46.499 --> 17:50.935
Little mark, he's just
like you were at that age.

17:51.070 --> 17:52.536
[sighs]

17:54.240 --> 17:59.576
You know, maybe god
does give second chances.

17:59.612 --> 18:01.545
I think I got something!
What do I do, what do I do?

18:01.614 --> 18:02.679
Bring it up!
Hand over hand!

18:02.715 --> 18:04.014
That's it, hand over hand!

18:04.050 --> 18:05.782
Come on, hand over hand,
you got it!

18:05.819 --> 18:09.453
Mike sr: Ho-ho-ho!
Pop: Oh!

18:09.456 --> 18:10.588
We did it!

18:10.590 --> 18:13.023
No, you did it.

18:13.059 --> 18:14.858
Well done.

18:14.894 --> 18:17.462
♪

18:17.597 --> 18:18.996
[laughs]

18:19.065 --> 18:22.533
Pop: Oh!
[laughs]

18:22.668 --> 18:24.001
Look!

18:24.003 --> 18:25.035
Is you alright?

18:25.105 --> 18:27.138
Fine, thanks!
Movin' on!

18:27.273 --> 18:28.339
No, no!
Wait, wait, wait!

18:28.341 --> 18:29.406
We need a tow!

18:29.476 --> 18:30.741
Yeah, alright.

18:30.810 --> 18:32.576
The motor's
just a little trouble.

18:32.612 --> 18:34.979
I could fix it,
but the lad here,

18:35.114 --> 18:36.180
He's a nervous nelly!

18:36.315 --> 18:38.282
[laughs]

18:40.453 --> 18:41.552
Adult mark:<i> I had</i>
<i> lost an uncle,</i>

18:41.621 --> 18:45.756
<i> And was about to gain</i>
<i> a grandmother.</i>

18:45.758 --> 18:47.691
Oh, we don't donate at the door.

18:47.693 --> 18:49.560
Oh, johanna clark?

18:49.596 --> 18:50.961
Johanna: Yes.

18:51.030 --> 18:52.429
My name's mark critch.

18:52.465 --> 18:54.565
Uh, we haven't met before,

18:54.601 --> 18:57.401
But I believe I'm your grandson?

18:57.437 --> 18:58.836
Husband: Who's at the door?

18:58.838 --> 19:01.706
Just... Someone
looking for donations.

19:01.841 --> 19:03.440
Husband: Get rid of them!

19:03.476 --> 19:04.642
What-- what do you want?

19:04.711 --> 19:06.711
Money?

19:06.713 --> 19:08.312
No, I just...

19:08.381 --> 19:11.549
Wanted to meet you.

19:11.551 --> 19:13.517
Well, you met me.

19:13.520 --> 19:15.052
Husband: Johanna?

19:15.121 --> 19:17.254
Some things are better
left buried in the past.

19:17.290 --> 19:19.089
I have a new life now.

19:19.091 --> 19:21.191
Don't come back here again.

19:28.635 --> 19:30.401
Adult mark:<i> The door</i>
<i> closed more firmly</i>

19:30.403 --> 19:33.404
<i> Than uncle brendan's</i>
<i> coffin lid.</i>

19:33.473 --> 19:36.741
♪

19:36.743 --> 19:39.510
♪

19:39.579 --> 19:41.345
Adult mark:<i> Mom had</i>
<i> come looking for me.</i>

19:41.347 --> 19:42.613
<i> And good thing, too.</i>

19:42.649 --> 19:44.748
<i> She had been hurt</i>
<i> by her mother before,</i>

19:44.883 --> 19:48.552
<i> And this apple hadn't fallen</i>
<i> far from the family tree.</i>

19:48.555 --> 19:50.754
You were right.

19:50.823 --> 19:52.556
She doesn't want to know me.

19:52.559 --> 19:56.160
♪

19:56.295 --> 20:00.030
♪

20:00.099 --> 20:01.164
Fox: You okay?

20:01.201 --> 20:04.168
Mark: [quietly]
yeah.

20:04.303 --> 20:07.771
[knocks loudly]

20:07.840 --> 20:10.174
Husband: Oh, for god's sake!

20:10.243 --> 20:14.378
Remember me?

20:14.380 --> 20:16.981
No point digging up old bones.

20:17.116 --> 20:20.317
You never even told him
about me, did ya?

20:20.353 --> 20:23.587
You old bat!

20:23.623 --> 20:25.122
Hi, there!

20:25.191 --> 20:27.124
I'm just her daughter
from the first marriage!

20:27.126 --> 20:30.527
Surprise, she's not
the vestal virgin you thought!

20:30.563 --> 20:31.529
Have fun with that.

20:31.664 --> 20:33.897
Johanna: You little bitch.

20:33.933 --> 20:35.599
No.

20:35.635 --> 20:37.567
It's critch.

20:40.406 --> 20:43.540
♪

20:43.576 --> 20:46.677
You know, you may not have
missed out on much with me,

20:46.713 --> 20:49.747
But you sure
missed out on my boys.

20:49.749 --> 20:53.884
Well, that's your loss,
not theirs.

20:53.886 --> 20:57.821
Come on, kids,
we're going home.

20:57.890 --> 21:00.891
♪

21:00.960 --> 21:02.994
Adult mark:<i> Every family</i>
<i> has a story.</i>

21:03.129 --> 21:06.230
<i> Some say we're who we are</i>
<i> because of who we come from.</i>

21:06.232 --> 21:07.565
<i> I disagree.</i>

21:07.700 --> 21:10.634
<i> We decide who we are</i>
<i> and who our family is.</i>

21:10.637 --> 21:13.838
<i> You live as long</i>
<i> as you're remembered.</i>

21:13.840 --> 21:18.042
<i> To me, my family</i>
<i> will live forever.</i>

21:18.177 --> 21:19.577
♪

21:19.712 --> 21:23.414
♪

21:23.483 --> 21:27.785
♪

21:27.787 --> 21:32.122
♪

21:32.158 --> 21:36.426
♪

21:36.462 --> 21:40.598
♪

21:40.733 --> 21:44.268
♪

21:44.403 --> 21:49.005
♪
